rndSysId.name: rndSysId
rndSysId.description: Identification of an RND device. The device type for each integer clarifies the sysObjectID in MIB - II.

rndAction.name: rndAction
rndAction.description: This variable enables the operator to perform one of the specified actions on the tables maintained by the network device. Send actions require support of proprietery File exchange protocol.

rndFileName.name: rndFileName
rndFileName.description: The name of the file used internally by RND for transferring tables maintained by network devices, using a prorietary File exchange protocol.

rndBridgeType.name: rndBridgeType
rndBridgeType.description: Identification of the RND bridge type.

rndInactiveArpTimeOut.name: rndInactiveArpTimeOut
rndInactiveArpTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum time period that can pass between ARP requests concerning an entry in the ARP table. After this time period, the entry is deleted from the table.

rndErrorDesc.name: rndErrorDesc
rndErrorDesc.description: A textual description of the enterprise-specific trap sent to the Network Management Station by the RND managed device.

rndErrorSeverity.name: rndErrorSeverity
rndErrorSeverity.description: The severity type of the enterprise-specific trap sent to the Network Management Station by the RND managed device.

rndBrgFeatures.name: rndBrgFeatures
rndBrgFeatures.description: A bit mask that defines the features supported by a particular configuration of this network element: __________________________________________ | Byte 1|Byte 2 |Byte 3 | ....|Byte 20 | |87654321| | 87654321| |________|_______________________________| Byte1 : bit1: TX Block mask bit2: Source Routing Encapulation bit3: SNA/SDLC bit4: Frame Relay bit5: SNMP bit6: LAN Manager bit7: High Performance bit8: Translation Byte2 : bit1: DEC Router bit2: IPX Router bit3: IP Router Byte3 : bit1: Dial Up Backup bit2: COD bit3: FACS bit4: Load Balance bit5: Remote Configuration bit6: RIP 2 bit7: OSPF bit8: IPX RIP/SAP Filter Byte4 : bit1: BootP Server bit2: BootP Client bit3: Compression bit4: V25.bis bit5: ISDN bit6: CODv2 bit7: NSPF bit8: UDP Relay Byte5 bit1:VirtualLAN bit2:Static IP Multicast bit3:IP Redundancy bit4:CCM2 bit5:ISDN Bonding bit6:Backup Link Selection -- for the VAN/Rdapter ver 4.0 bit7:IP/IPX Forwarding -- for the WANgate ver 4.0 bit8:Improved COD Byte6 bit1: Server Disptacher bit2: ISDN_US -- for the VANSX/WANGATE ver 5.0 bit3: PPP bit4: IP Rip Filter -- for Vgate3 bit5: Zero Hop Routing -- for Vgate3 bit6: ISDN Japan Byte7 bit1: With unmanaged Switch bit2: 2 LANs bit3: OSPF Ver 2.0 bit4: FACS Ver 2.0 bit5: Multiple WEB Farm bit6: Backup Server

rndBrgLicense.name: rndBrgLicense
rndBrgLicense.description: This parameter is used for entering a s/w license number for a device. A separate license number is supplied for each device.

rndICMPTransmitionEnable.name: rndICMPTransmitionEnable
rndICMPTransmitionEnable.description: This variable controlls the ability to transmit ICMP frames

rndCommunityTable.name: rndCommunityTable
rndCommunityTable.description: The community table of the agent

rndCommunityEntry.name: rndCommunityEntry
rndCommunityEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndCommunityMngStationAddr.name: rndCommunityMngStationAddr
rndCommunityMngStationAddr.description: The management station that will be allowed to communicate with the agent IP address

rndCommunityString.name: rndCommunityString
rndCommunityString.description: The community string with which the management station will communicate with the agent

rndCommunityAccess.name: rndCommunityAccess
rndCommunityAccess.description: The allowed access to this management station

rndCommunityTrapsEnable.name: rndCommunityTrapsEnable
rndCommunityTrapsEnable.description: Should the agent send traps to the management station

rndCommunityStatus.name: rndCommunityStatus
rndCommunityStatus.description: The status of this entry. If the status is invalid the community entry will be deleted

rndManagedTime.name: rndManagedTime
rndManagedTime.description: The time will be sent in the format hhmmss

rndManagedDate.name: rndManagedDate
rndManagedDate.description: The date will be sent in the format ddmmyyyy

genGroupHWVersion.name: genGroupHWVersion
genGroupHWVersion.description: Defines the HW version of the product.

genGroupConfigurationSymbol.name: genGroupConfigurationSymbol
genGroupConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by LANNET. One single character A..Z defines the CS version.

genGroupHWStatus.name: genGroupHWStatus
genGroupHWStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

rndIfTable.name: rndIfTable
rndIfTable.description: RND-specific interface table. Each table entry includes an index, Board number, Network Address, interface status, clock indicator and interface cost.

rndIfEntry.name: rndIfEntry
rndIfEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndIfIndex.name: rndIfIndex
rndIfIndex.description: Index to the RND Interface Table. The interface defined by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex (MIBII).

rndIfBoardNum.name: rndIfBoardNum
rndIfBoardNum.description: The interface defined by this entry correspTnds to the board defined by the same value of rndSlotBoardNum in the rndSlotTab.

rndIfNetAddress.name: rndIfNetAddress
rndIfNetAddress.description: The IP address of the interface defined by the particular value of rndIfIndex.

rndIfStatus.name: rndIfStatus
rndIfStatus.description: The current status of the interface.

rndIfClockType.name: rndIfClockType
rndIfClockType.description: rndIfClockType defines the type of clock each interface uses: internal or external.

rndIfBaudRate.name: rndIfBaudRate
rndIfBaudRate.description: Defines the baud rate of use by the interface. The valid rates are determined by the type of the media for which this baud rate is defined.

rndIfCost.name: rndIfCost
rndIfCost.description: This variable assigns a transmission cost to the interface (channel or LAN). These costs are used in Level II routing. The costs aretypically inversly proportional to the channel quality.

rndIfCompression.name: rndIfCompression
rndIfCompression.description: Defines whether data compression is enabled or disabled for the interface.

rndIfCompressionStatus.name: rndIfCompressionStatus
rndIfCompressionStatus.description: Defines the status of the compression component: not-inserted - Compression component is not in the device active - Compression is enabled and operates correctly not-active - Compression is enables but does not operate. The reason may be that there is no compression component on the device connected to this interface. disabled - Compression was disabled by management, using variable rndCompression.

rndIfCompressionRate.name: rndIfCompressionRate
rndIfCompressionRate.description: Percentage of compression. This variable applies only if rndCompressionStatus is active.

rndIfCompressionType.name: rndIfCompressionType
rndIfCompressionType.description: This parameter indicates the type of compression option available in the device. none(1) - indicates that there is no compression option in the device lowSpeed(2) - indicates a compression option which is operational up to line speed sof 64 kbps. highSpeed(3)- indicates a compression option which is operational up to line speeds of 2 Mbps.

rndIfFilterMode.name: rndIfFilterMode
rndIfFilterMode.description: This parameter indicates the type of filtering in the device.

rndIfChannelType.name: rndIfChannelType
rndIfChannelType.description: The type of the WAN channel

rndIfBridge.name: rndIfBridge
rndIfBridge.description: This variable indicates whether this interface forward Layer II pakages.

rndHighPriorityIf.name: rndHighPriorityIf
rndHighPriorityIf.description: This variable indicates whether this interface will forward pakages that fit HighPriority set by the manager.

rndWanHeader.name: rndWanHeader
rndWanHeader.description: This variable indicates the RND WAN header type used for frames which pass through this interface. 'regular' specifies a 14 bytes header compatible with older OG versions and 'short' a 4 byte header compatible with the RND adapter product family.

rndDuplexMode.name: rndDuplexMode
rndDuplexMode.description: This variable indicates whether this interface operates in half duplex full duplex or auto negotiation mode.

rndFACSDefaultAction.name: rndFACSDefaultAction
rndFACSDefaultAction.description: Used to define the default action for the device, when no FACS statements applicable to a given frame are defined.

rndFACSActEntry.name: rndFACSActEntry
rndFACSActEntry.description: Each rndFACSActEntry consist of the following parameters

rndFACSActType.name: rndFACSActType
rndFACSActType.description: This parameter indicate on which FACS Table the FACS action will preform.

rndFACSActIfIndex.name: rndFACSActIfIndex
rndFACSActIfIndex.description: The interface to which this FACS entry is applicable.

rndFACSAction.name: rndFACSAction
rndFACSAction.description: The management station that sends a SET request for one of these actions with indexes rndFACSType and rndFACSIfIndex defines the type and the interface Id for which all FACS statements are to be erased. If no interface or no type is specified, all FACS statements for a protocol are erased.

rndFACSEntry.name: rndFACSEntry
rndFACSEntry.description: Each FACS statment consist of the following parameters

rndFACSIfIndex.name: rndFACSIfIndex
rndFACSIfIndex.description: The interface to which this FACS entry is applicable.

rndFACSProtocolType.name: rndFACSProtocolType
rndFACSProtocolType.description: This parameter define the protocol the Security Access Control is applicable.

rndFACSType.name: rndFACSType
rndFACSType.description: The Mode of in which this FACS statement operates.

rndFACSSrcAdd.name: rndFACSSrcAdd
rndFACSSrcAdd.description: The size of the octet string will be according to the protocol type define in rndFACSProtocolType.

rndFACSDesAdd.name: rndFACSDesAdd
rndFACSDesAdd.description: Destination-address The size of the octet string will be according to the protocol type define in rndFACSProtocolType .

rndFACSSoketNum.name: rndFACSSoketNum
rndFACSSoketNum.description: Port/socket number for different applications 0 is default meaning not applicable.

rndFACSMask1Id.name: rndFACSMask1Id
rndFACSMask1Id.description: Index into RND mask table FACS/COD Type) .

rndFACSMask2Id.name: rndFACSMask2Id
rndFACSMask2Id.description: Index into RND mask table FACS/COD according to the value of rndFACSType .

rndFACSStatus.name: rndFACSStatus
rndFACSStatus.description: The status of a table entry.

rndBootPServerAddress.name: rndBootPServerAddress
rndBootPServerAddress.description: The IPAddress of the BOOTP server. the OpenGate will act as a BootP relay if this parameter is not equale to 0.0.0.0.

rndBootPRelaySecThreshold.name: rndBootPRelaySecThreshold
rndBootPRelaySecThreshold.description: BootP requests are relayed only if their SEC field is greater or equal to the threshold value in order to allow local BootP Servers to answer first.

rsIpAddrTable.name: rsIpAddrTable
rsIpAddrTable.description: This table is parralel to MIB II IpAddrTable, and is used to add/delete entries to/from that table. In addition it contains private objects.

rsIpAddrEntry.name: rsIpAddrEntry
rsIpAddrEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this entity's IP addresses.

rsIpAdEntAddr.name: rsIpAdEntAddr
rsIpAdEntAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

rsIpAdEntIfIndex.name: rsIpAdEntIfIndex
rsIpAdEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

rsIpAdEntNetMask.name: rsIpAdEntNetMask
rsIpAdEntNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

rsIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast.name: rsIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast
rsIpAdEntForwardIpBroadcast.description: This variable controls forwarding of IP (sub)net-directed broadcasts destined for an attached sub(net).

rsIpAdEntReasmMaxSize.name: rsIpAdEntReasmMaxSize
rsIpAdEntReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.

rsIpAdEntStatus.name: rsIpAdEntStatus
rsIpAdEntStatus.description: The validity of this entry. Invalid indicates that this entry is invalid in IpAddrTable (MIB II).

rsIpAdEntBcastAddr.name: rsIpAdEntBcastAddr
rsIpAdEntBcastAddr.description: Indicates how the host part of ip subnet broadcast messages will be filled: 0 - host part will be filled by 0 1 - host part will be filled by 1.

rsIpAdEntVlanTag.name: rsIpAdEntVlanTag
rsIpAdEntVlanTag.description: The vlan Tag value that represent this ip interface this filed include both vlna tag and vlan priority

rsIcmpGenErrMsgEnable.name: rsIcmpGenErrMsgEnable
rsIcmpGenErrMsgEnable.description: This variable controlls the ability to generate ICMP error messages

rsIcmpRdTable.name: rsIcmpRdTable
rsIcmpRdTable.description: This table contains ICMP Router Discovery parameters configurated per IP interface.

rsIcmpRdEntry.name: rsIcmpRdEntry
rsIcmpRdEntry.description: The ICMP parameters configurated for IP interface.

rsIcmpRdIpAddr.name: rsIcmpRdIpAddr
rsIcmpRdIpAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's information pertains.

rsIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr.name: rsIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr
rsIcmpRdIpAdvertAddr.description: The IP destination address to be used for multicast Router Advertisements sent from the interface. The only permissible values are the all-systems multicast address, 224.0.0.1, or the limited-broadcast address, 255.255.255.255.

rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.name: rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval
rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending multicast Router Advertisements from the interface, in seconds. Must be no less than 4 seconds and no greater than 1800 seconds.

rsIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval.name: rsIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval
rsIcmpRdMinAdvertInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface, in seconds. Must be no less than 3 seconds and no greater than rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval. Default: 0.75 * rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.

rsIcmpRdAdvertLifetime.name: rsIcmpRdAdvertLifetime
rsIcmpRdAdvertLifetime.description: The maximum length of time that the advertised addresses are to be considered as valid. Must be no less than rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval and no greater than 9000 seconds. Default: 3 * rsIcmpRdMaxAdvertInterval.

rsIcmpRdAdvertise.name: rsIcmpRdAdvertise
rsIcmpRdAdvertise.description: A flag indicating whether or not the address is to be advertised.

rsIcmpRdPreferenceLevel.name: rsIcmpRdPreferenceLevel
rsIcmpRdPreferenceLevel.description: The preferability of the address as a default router address, relative to other router addresses on the same subnet.

rsIcmpRdEntStatus.name: rsIcmpRdEntStatus
rsIcmpRdEntStatus.description: Setting of any value to this object set values of all fields to the default values.

rsRip2IfConfTable.name: rsRip2IfConfTable
rsRip2IfConfTable.description: This table is extension of rip2IfConfTable (RFC 1389 ,RIP 2)

rsRip2IfConfAddress.name: rsRip2IfConfAddress
rsRip2IfConfAddress.description: The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet.

rsRip2IfConfVirtualDis.name: rsRip2IfConfVirtualDis
rsRip2IfConfVirtualDis.description: This variable defines the virtual number of hops assigned to the interface specified by rsIfIpAddrIndex. This enables fine-tuning of the RIP routing algorithm.

rsRip2IfConfAutoSend.name: rsRip2IfConfAutoSend
rsRip2IfConfAutoSend.description: This variable controls RIP automatic send behavior. If enabled and no routers were heard on the interface, RIP will only send default route with high metric. Otherwise RIP will send updates according to configuration.

rsArpDeleteTable.name: rsArpDeleteTable
rsArpDeleteTable.description: Setting this object to any not-null value has the effect of deleting all entries of the ARP table.

rsArpInactiveTimeOut.name: rsArpInactiveTimeOut
rsArpInactiveTimeOut.description: This variable defines the maximum time period (in second) that can pass between ARP requests concerning an entry in the ARP table. After this time period, the entry is deleted from the table.

rsArpProxy.name: rsArpProxy
rsArpProxy.description: When ARP Proxy is enabled, the router can respond to ARP requests for nodes located on a different sub-net, provided they are it its network table. The router responds with its own MAC address. When ARP Proxy is disabled, the router responds only to ARP requests for its own IP addresses.

rsSendConfigFile.name: rsSendConfigFile
rsSendConfigFile.description: The file name include path where the Router Server will put the full configuration. The default destination address will be the sender address.

rsGetConfigFile.name: rsGetConfigFile
rsGetConfigFile.description: The file name include path where the Router Server will get the configuration. The default source address will be the sender address.

rsLoadSoftware.name: rsLoadSoftware
rsLoadSoftware.description: The file name include path where the Router Server will get the software. The source address will the sender address.

rsFileServerAddress.name: rsFileServerAddress
rsFileServerAddress.description: The IP address of the configuration / sw server.

ipRedundAdminStatus.name: ipRedundAdminStatus
ipRedundAdminStatus.description: This variable controls the IP Redundancy method in the device. In case the value is enable, it means the ARP redundancy mechanism is running .If the value is vrrp, it means the former redundancy mechanism is disabled, and the vrrp mechanism is enabled. If the value is disable, both redundancy methods are disabled

ipRedundRoutersTable.name: ipRedundRoutersTable
ipRedundRoutersTable.description: List of IP addresses backed up by this router.

ipRedundRoutersEntry.name: ipRedundRoutersEntry
ipRedundRoutersEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

ipRedundRoutersIfAddr.name: ipRedundRoutersIfAddr
ipRedundRoutersIfAddr.description: The Ip address of the IP interface on which the redundancy feature is operational.

ipRedundRoutersMainRouterAddr.name: ipRedundRoutersMainRouterAddr
ipRedundRoutersMainRouterAddr.description: The Ip address of the polled main router.

ipRedundRoutersOperStatus.name: ipRedundRoutersOperStatus
ipRedundRoutersOperStatus.description: If active, the main router is considered inoperational and the IP interface operates as its backup.

ipRedundRoutersPollInterval.name: ipRedundRoutersPollInterval
ipRedundRoutersPollInterval.description: Polling interval for this router (in seconds). If 0 the router is not polled.

ipRedundRoutersTimeout.name: ipRedundRoutersTimeout
ipRedundRoutersTimeout.description: Interval in seconds during which the backed-up router must signal. If it does not signal, it is considered inoperational and the IP interface starts operating as backup.

ipLeakStaticToRip.name: ipLeakStaticToRip
ipLeakStaticToRip.description: This parameter controls leaking (redistribution) of static routes to RIP. When enabled, all routes inserted to the IP routing table via SNMP are advertised into RIP.

ipLeakStaticToOspf.name: ipLeakStaticToOspf
ipLeakStaticToOspf.description: This parameter controls leaking (redistribution) of static routes into OSPF. When enabled, all routes inserted to the IP routing table via SNMP are advertised into OSPF as external routes.

ipLeakOspfToRip.name: ipLeakOspfToRip
ipLeakOspfToRip.description: This parameter controls leaking (redistribution) of routes from OSPF to RIP. If enabled, all routes learned via OSPF are advertised into RIP.

ipLeakRipToOspf.name: ipLeakRipToOspf
ipLeakRipToOspf.description: This parameter controls leaking (redistribution) of routes from RIP to OSPF. If enabled, all routes learned via RIP are advertised into OSPF as external routes.

ipLeakExtDirectToOspf.name: ipLeakExtDirectToOspf
ipLeakExtDirectToOspf.description: This parameter controls leaking (redistribution) into OSPF of direct routes external to OSPF, i.e. routes to local network corresponding to IP interfaces on which OSPF is disabled. When enabled, all such direct routes are advertised into OSPF as external routes.

rsIpRipFilterGlbTable.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbTable
rsIpRipFilterGlbTable.description: The table of RIP global filters per IP router.

rsIpRipFilterGlbEntry.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbEntry
rsIpRipFilterGlbEntry.description: An entry in the RIP global filter table

rsIpRipFilterGlbStatus.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbStatus
rsIpRipFilterGlbStatus.description: The validity of this entry. Setting this value to invalid deletes the entry, and the entry may be actualy removed from the table.

rsIpRipFilterGlbIpAddr.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbIpAddr
rsIpRipFilterGlbIpAddr.description: network prefix IP address, as in the forwarding table.

rsIpRipFilterGlbNetworkMaskBits.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbNetworkMaskBits
rsIpRipFilterGlbNetworkMaskBits.description: the number of bits in the IP Network mask, called network-prefix-length in Router Requirements terminology. for example: the value 16 means mask 255.255.0.0

rsIpRipFilterGlbMatchBits.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbMatchBits
rsIpRipFilterGlbMatchBits.description: the number of bits to match in the Network IP address. A value smaller than 32 defines a wildcard. for example: the value 8 means all routes whose leftmost 8 bits are equal to those of the network IP address. If this variable has a value other than 32, than rsIpRipFilterGlbNetworkMaskBits must be 0 and is ignored.

rsIpRipFilterGlbAction.name: rsIpRipFilterGlbAction
rsIpRipFilterGlbAction.description: Filter action - permit/deny for this network

rsIpRipFilterLclTable.name: rsIpRipFilterLclTable
rsIpRipFilterLclTable.description: Table of input/output RIP filters used per IP Interface.

rsIpRipFilterLclEntry.name: rsIpRipFilterLclEntry
rsIpRipFilterLclEntry.description: An entry in the Intf RIP filter table

rsIpRipFilterLclIpIntf.name: rsIpRipFilterLclIpIntf
rsIpRipFilterLclIpIntf.description: The IP address identifying the RIP interface for this filter. This value corresponds to rsIpAdEntAddr.

rsIpRipFilterLclNumber.name: rsIpRipFilterLclNumber
rsIpRipFilterLclNumber.description: Number of RIP filter for this Interface

rsIpRipFilterLclStatus.name: rsIpRipFilterLclStatus
rsIpRipFilterLclStatus.description: The validity of this entry. Setting this value to invalid deletes the entry, and the entry may be actualy removed from the table.

rsIpRipFilterLclIpAddr.name: rsIpRipFilterLclIpAddr
rsIpRipFilterLclIpAddr.description: network prefix IP address, as in the forwarding table.

rsIpRipFilterLclNetworkMaskBits.name: rsIpRipFilterLclNetworkMaskBits
rsIpRipFilterLclNetworkMaskBits.description: the number of bits in the IP Network mask, called network-prefix-length in Router Requirements terminology. for example: the value 16 means mask 255.255.0.0

rsIpRipFilterLclMatchBits.name: rsIpRipFilterLclMatchBits
rsIpRipFilterLclMatchBits.description: the number of bits to match in the Network IP address. A value smaller than 32 defines a wildcard. for example: the value 8 means all routes whose leftmost 8 bits are equal to those of the network IP address. If this variable has a value other than 32, than rsIpRipFilterLclNetworkMaskBits must be 0 and is ignored.

virtualLanTable.name: virtualLanTable
virtualLanTable.description: An entry of this table specifies an new ifIndex with a type of propVirtual(53).

virtualLanEntry.name: virtualLanEntry
virtualLanEntry.description: A list of information for each virtual LAN.

vlIfIndex.name: vlIfIndex
vlIfIndex.description: An logical interface number, corresponded this VL

vlProto.name: vlProto
vlProto.description: The protocol, supported by this VL. The meanings of the values are: other: none of the following. This VL includes any protocol except the following protocols. It is a bridging VL. RS relies on a third-party router to exchange traffic between nodes on different virtual LANs of this type. IP: This is a routing VL, RS will route between nodes on different virtual LANs. IPmulticast: RS will broadcast the message to all the VL's ports. Used for video-conferencing applications. ipxRaw: This is a Routing VL, RS will route between nodes on different virtual LANs. ipxET: This is a routing VL, RS will route between nodes on different virtual LANs. ipxLLC: This is a routing VL, RS will route between nodes on different virtual LANs. ipxSNAP: This is a routing VL, RS will route between nodes on different virtual LANs. decNET: This is a bridging VL, RS relies on a third-party router to exchange traffic between nodes on different DECnet virtual LANs of this type. netBios: This is a Bridging VL, RS relies on a third-party router to exchange traffic between nodes on different NetBIOS virtual LANs of this type. appleTalk: This is a bridging VL, RS relies on a third-party router to exchange traffic between nodes on different AppleTalk virtual LANs of this type.

vlAutoConfigEnable.name: vlAutoConfigEnable
vlAutoConfigEnable.description: It is used only in the case of IP. The meanings of the values are: true(1): Autolearning is used for this VL false(2): Autolearning isn't used for this VL from ports, specified in the table virtualLanAutoConfTable.

vlStatus.name: vlStatus
vlStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry

vlType.name: vlType
vlType.description: regular - ordinary type specBroadcast - for switches that support VLANs as a set of ports and only as a broadcast domain: broadcast frames do not cross VLAN's bounders, but unicast frames may be transmitted between different VLANs. Permits passing of broadcast frames between Vgate's VLANs. specArpReq - for switches that support VLANs as a set of ports and only as a broadcast domain: broadcast frames do not cross VLAN's bounders, but unicast frames may be transmitted between different VLANs. Permits passing of ARP request frames between Vgate's VLANs. specBroadcastAndUnicast - for switches that support VLANs as a set of ports but no frame crosses VLAN's bounders. Permits passing of IP/ARP request broadcast and IP unicast frames between Vgate's VLANs. specArpReqAndUnicast - for switches that support VLANs as a set of ports but no frame crosses VLAN's bounders. Permits passing of ARP request broadcast and IP unicast frames between Vgate's VLANs. This type can be used only for IP VLANs.

virtualLanPortsTable.name: virtualLanPortsTable
virtualLanPortsTable.description: For each VL (a ifIndex with a type of propVirtual(53)) an entry of this table specifies a set of ports, which it contains.

virtualLanPortEntry.name: virtualLanPortEntry
virtualLanPortEntry.description: A entry of this table specifies a VL and a port belonging to it

vLIfIndex.name: vLIfIndex
vLIfIndex.description: An logical interface number, corresponding to this VL

vLPortIfIndex.name: vLPortIfIndex
vLPortIfIndex.description: A physical port belonging to the VL specified by vlIfIndex.

vLPortType.name: vLPortType
vLPortType.description: static means configured by user dynamic means autoconfigured by the RS

vLPortStatus.name: vLPortStatus
vLPortStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry

virtualLanAutoConfTable.name: virtualLanAutoConfTable
virtualLanAutoConfTable.description: This table specifies per a routing protocol a set of ports, from which RS will automatically learning VL in accordance with rules, defined by the protocol.

virtualLanAutoConfEntry.name: virtualLanAutoConfEntry
virtualLanAutoConfEntry.description: One port, specified by vlAutoConfPortIfIndex, for which the RS will automatically learn its VL in accordance with rules, defined by the protocol specified in vlAutoConfProto.

vlAutoConfPortIfIndex.name: vlAutoConfPortIfIndex
vlAutoConfPortIfIndex.description: Port on which the autoconfig option should be supported

vlAutoConfProto.name: vlAutoConfProto
vlAutoConfProto.description: Protocol for which the autoconfig option is supported for the port specified by vlAutoConfPortIfIndex

vlAutoConfStatus.name: vlAutoConfStatus
vlAutoConfStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry

virtualLanAutoConfAgingTimeout.name: virtualLanAutoConfAgingTimeout
virtualLanAutoConfAgingTimeout.description: The units of this MIB object is seconds. Its value can be either 0 or in range 10..65535 .

rsIfConfTable.name: rsIfConfTable
rsIfConfTable.description: This table enable the user to add interface to the RS. RS will automatically add the new interface to the interface Table

rsIfConfEntry.name: rsIfConfEntry
rsIfConfEntry.description: Each entry defines a configured interface.

rsIfConfIndex.name: rsIfConfIndex
rsIfConfIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the interface. It is used as a cross reference in other system tables

rsIfConfType.name: rsIfConfType

reaSrcAddrValidationEnable.description: The Platform will verify the source address of incoming IP datagram.

rsMaxIpxFrwEntriesAfterReset.description: Future maximal number of entries in Ipx forwarding table.

rsMaxRoutingEntriesAfterReset.description: Future maximal number of entries in the routing table.

rndAlarmEnabling.description: Indicates whether alarms should be issued to the high-level NMS

rndAlarmInterval.name: rndAlarmInterval
rndAlarmInterval.description: Indicates the minimal period of time which must pass after issuing an alarm before issuing the same alarm again.

rndMonitoredElementsTable.name: rndMonitoredElementsTable
rndMonitoredElementsTable.description: The table of monitored elements of the network

rndMonitoredElementEntry.name: rndMonitoredElementEntry
rndMonitoredElementEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMonitoredElementAddress.description: The IP address of the monitored element

rndMonitoredElementCommunity.name: rndMonitoredElementCommunity
rndMonitoredElementCommunity.description: The community of the monitored element

rndMonitoredElementLabel.description: The label assigned by the network manager to the monitored element

rndDefaultPollingInterval.name: rndDefaultPollingInterval
rndDefaultPollingInterval.description: The default period of time between two consecutive pollings of the monitored element for the value of an object instance. If no other polling interval is specifically assigned to the monitored object instance, this one will be used

rndDefaultLogFile.name: rndDefaultLogFile
rndDefaultLogFile.description: The default file path of the log-file which will contain the polling results for the monitored element. If no other file path is specifically assigned to the monitored object instance, this log-file will be used.

rndMonitoredElementStatus.name: rndMonitoredElementStatus
rndMonitoredElementStatus.description: It is used to manage the monitored elements table and indicates the current monitoring status of an element.

rndMonitoringTable.name: rndMonitoringTable
rndMonitoringTable.description: The table of monitored object instances. Each monitored object instance belongs to a monitored element previously entered in the rndMonitoredElementsTable.

rndMonitoringEntry.name: rndMonitoringEntry
rndMonitoringEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMonitoredElement.name: rndMonitoredElement
rndMonitoredElement.description: A label assigned by the network manager to a monitored element to which this monitored object instance belongs. This label must have been previously entered in an instance of rndMonitoredElementLabel

rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel.name: rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel
rndMonitoredObjectInstanceLabel.description: The label assigned by the network manager to the monitored object instance

rndMonitoredObjectName.name: rndMonitoredObjectName
rndMonitoredObjectName.description: The symbolic object type name of the object to which the monitored object instance belongs (as it appears the MIB module definition). In case of ambiguity the <MIB module name> : <object type name> format should be used. An instance of rndMonitoredObjectName need not be assigned any value, if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier is assigned a value, since any one of these, together with the object instance identifier, suffices to unambigously identify the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier.name: rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier
rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier.description: The object identifier of the object to which the monitored object instance belongs. An instance of rndMonitoredObjectIdentifier need not be assigned any value, if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectName is assigned a value, since any one of these, together with the object instance identifier, suffices to unambigously identify the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectInstance.name: rndMonitoredObjectInstance
rndMonitoredObjectInstance.description: The instance identifier (key) of the monitored object instance.

rndMonitoredObjectSyntax.name: rndMonitoredObjectSyntax
rndMonitoredObjectSyntax.description: The syntax of the monitored object instance (i.e., the syntax of the object type of the object to which the monitored instance belongs). Need not be assigned any value if the corresponding instance of rndMonitoredObjectName has been assigned a value

rndMonitoringInterval.name: rndMonitoringInterval
rndMonitoringInterval.description: The period of time between two consecutive retrievals of the monitored object instance's value.

rndAlarmMaxTreshold.name: rndAlarmMaxTreshold
rndAlarmMaxTreshold.description: The value of the monitored object instance, the exceeding of which will cause the generation of an alarm to the high-level management station.

rndAlarmMinTreshold.name: rndAlarmMinTreshold
rndAlarmMinTreshold.description: If the value of the monitored object instance falls below the value assigned to rndAlarmMinTreshold, an alarm to the high-level management station will be issued.

rndMonitoringLogfile.name: rndMonitoringLogfile
rndMonitoringLogfile.description: The entire path of the file in which the results of the monitoring of this object instance should be recorded.

rndMonitoringEntryStatus.name: rndMonitoringEntryStatus
rndMonitoringEntryStatus.description: It is used to manage the monitored object instances table and indicates the current monitoring status of an object instance.

rndMibFilesTable.name: rndMibFilesTable
rndMibFilesTable.description: The table of monitored object instances. Each monitored object instance belongs to a monitored element previously entered in the rndMonitoredElementsTable.

rndMibFileEntry.name: rndMibFileEntry
rndMibFileEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rndMibFileIndex.name: rndMibFileIndex
rndMibFileIndex.description: The number of the MIB file in the list MIB files supported by the Mid-Level management station. The order of the MIB files in this list must reflect the the IMPORT relation between the MIBS contained in the MIB files, i.e., if MIB A IMPORTS FROM MIB B, the file containing MIB A must have a lesser index in this table than the file containing MIB B.

rndMibFilePath.name: rndMibFilePath
rndMibFilePath.description: The path of the MIB file in the MIB file server.

rndMibFileRefresh.name: rndMibFileRefresh
rndMibFileRefresh.description: Indicates if the file should be fetched after setting this entry from the MIB file server.

rndMibFileEntryStatus.name: rndMibFileEntryStatus
rndMibFileEntryStatus.description: It is used to manage the MIB files table.

rndHardwareConfiguration.name: rndHardwareConfiguration
rndHardwareConfiguration.description: Indicates whether the current SET SNMP PDU contains hardware configuration (i.e., normally read-only variables). SET of such variables in the Mid-level management station will be allowed only if this variable is included in the SNMP PDU and its value is true. Its value as returned in a GET SNMP PDU will always be false.

rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration.name: rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration
rndEraseSimulatedConfiguration.description: eraseSimulatedConfiguration instructs the MLNMS to erase all the simulated configuration from its configuration data-base (CDB). This the only accepted value for SNMP SET statements and will never be returned in SNMP GET statements. simulatedConfigurationPresent indicates that the MLNMS currently has a simulated configuration. simulatedConfigurationErased indicates that the MLNMS currently has no simulated configuration.

rndDeleteValuesTable.name: rndDeleteValuesTable
rndDeleteValuesTable.description: This table indicates which MIB variables are row status fields which control the status of the entry to which they belong. This table also indicates which (integer!) value of these MIB variables will cause, if present in a SNMP SET PDU, the deletion of the conceptual row instance to which the SET MIB variable instance belongs.

rndDeleteValuesEntry.name: rndDeleteValuesEntry
rndDeleteValuesEntry.description: The row definition for the rndDeleteValuesTable table.

rndRowStatusVariableName.name: rndRowStatusVariableName
rndRowStatusVariableName.description: The name of the row status field. This name may not necessarily be any name which is present in the MIBs loaded into the MLNMS station.

rndRowStatusObjectId.name: rndRowStatusObjectId
rndRowStatusObjectId.description: The object id of the row status field. If the rndRowStatusVariableName is a name present in the MIBs loaded into the MLNMS, this MIB variable is not required, but if given, it must match the object id known to the MLNMS. The variable identified by rndRowStatusVariableName and/or rndRowStatusObjectId must be a read-write MIB variable of type INTEGER which belongs to an entry (i.e, is a child of a MIB variable of type SEQUENCE).

rndRowDeleteValue.name: rndRowDeleteValue
rndRowDeleteValue.description: The value of the variable identified by rndRowStatusVariableName and/or rndRowStatusObjectId, which, if present in a SNMP SET PDU, will cause the deletion of the conceptual row instance which the SET MIB variable instance belongs.

rndDeleteValueEntryStatus.name: rndDeleteValueEntryStatus
rndDeleteValueEntryStatus.description: It is used to delete an entry from this table.

rsIpZhrGeneralStatus.name: rsIpZhrGeneralStatus
rsIpZhrGeneralStatus.description: This parameter enables or disables the IP Zero Hop Routing feature for all IP interfaces. The IP Zero Hop Routing feature can also be enabled or disabled on each IP interface through the rsIpZhrStatusTable.

rsIpZhrAgingTimeout.name: rsIpZhrAgingTimeout
rsIpZhrAgingTimeout.description: This parameter controls the aging time-out in seconds of direct connections which were allocated. The virtual IP address of a direct connection whose time-out has expired is eligible for allocation to a different connection.

rsIpZhrStatusTable.name: rsIpZhrStatusTable
rsIpZhrStatusTable.description: The administrative status of the ZHR feature per ip interface.

rsIpZhrStatusEntry.name: rsIpZhrStatusEntry
rsIpZhrStatusEntry.description: An entry in the ZHR status table.

rsIpZhrStatusIpIntf.name: rsIpZhrStatusIpIntf
rsIpZhrStatusIpIntf.description: The Ip interface whose ZHR feature status is accessed.

rsIpZhrAdminStatus.name: rsIpZhrAdminStatus
rsIpZhrAdminStatus.description: It is used to control whether ZHR will operate on the interface.

rsIpZhrVirtAddressTable.name: rsIpZhrVirtAddressTable
rsIpZhrVirtAddressTable.description: The table of free virtual IP addresses which may be allocated to establish direct connections - Per IP Interface.

rsIpZhrVirtAddressEntry.description: An entry in the ZHR virtual IP addresses table

rsIpZhrVirtAddressIpIntf.name: rsIpZhrVirtAddressIpIntf
rsIpZhrVirtAddressIpIntf.description: The Ip Interface to which the IP addresses in this entry are allocated.

rsIpZhrVirtAddressTo.name: rsIpZhrVirtAddressTo
rsIpZhrVirtAddressTo.description: The last free IP address in the block.

rsIpZhrVirtAddressFrom.name: rsIpZhrVirtAddressFrom
rsIpZhrVirtAddressFrom.description: The first free IP address in the block.

rsIpZhrVirtAddressStatus.name: rsIpZhrVirtAddressStatus
rsIpZhrVirtAddressStatus.description: It is used to manage the virtual address table. The supported actions will be active, createAndGo and destroy.

rsIpZhrConnectionsTable.description: Table of the currently active direct connections.

rsIpZhrConnectionEntry.description: An entry in the ZHR Connection table

rsIpZhrConnectionIpIntf.name: rsIpZhrConnectionIpIntf
rsIpZhrConnectionIpIntf.description: The IP Interface for which this direct connection was established.

rsIpZhrConnectionSrcIp.name: rsIpZhrConnectionSrcIp
rsIpZhrConnectionSrcIp.description: The source IP Address of this direct connection.

rsIpZhrConnectionDestIp.name: rsIpZhrConnectionDestIp
rsIpZhrConnectionDestIp.description: The destination IP Address of this direct connection.

rsIpZhrConnectionVirtualIp.name: rsIpZhrConnectionVirtualIp
rsIpZhrConnectionVirtualIp.description: The virtual IP address allocated for this direct connection.

rsIpZhrConnectionType.name: rsIpZhrConnectionType
rsIpZhrConnectionType.description: The type of this direct connection. dynamic - established by the RS. disabled - established by the RS. The RS detected that the virtual address is already used as destination by the source BEFORE its allocation, and therefore marked this connection as 'disabled' to prevent a future allocation of this virtual address to this source. static - established by user.

rsIpZhrConnectionAge.name: rsIpZhrConnectionAge
rsIpZhrConnectionAge.description: The age of the connection in seconds.

rsIpZhrConnectionStatus.name: rsIpZhrConnectionStatus
rsIpZhrConnectionStatus.description: It is used to manage the connections table. The supported actions will be active, createAndGo and destroy.

routeTableOverflow.name: routeTableOverflow
routeTableOverflow.description: An overflow condition has occurred in the Routing Table. The Routing Table is used for IP routing algorithm (RIP).

resetRequired.name: resetRequired
resetRequired.description: This trap indicates that in order to perform the last SET request, a reset operation of the router/bridge is required. This occurs when the layer 2 routing algorithm is changed between SPF and Spanning Tree. The reset can be performed manually or using the variable rndAction.

endTftp.name: endTftp
endTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device finished a TFTP transaction with the management station. variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

abortTftp.name: abortTftp
abortTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device aborted a TFTP session with the management station. variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

startTftp.name: startTftp
startTftp.description: Informational trap indicating that the device has intiated a TFTP session. rndErrorDesc will contain the file type in question

ipxRipTblOverflow.name: ipxRipTblOverflow
ipxRipTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX RIP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

ipxSapTblOverflow.name: ipxSapTblOverflow
ipxSapTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX SAP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

facsAccessVoilation.name: facsAccessVoilation
facsAccessVoilation.description: This trap indicates that message that fits FACS statenebt with operation blockAndReport was forward to the interface.The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== info ) and interface Number.

autoConfigurationCompleted.name: autoConfigurationCompleted
autoConfigurationCompleted.description: This trap indicates that auto comfiguration completetd succssefully. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== info )

forwardingTabOverflow.name: forwardingTabOverflow
forwardingTabOverflow.description: This trap indicates that an overflow condition has occurred in the layer II Forward Table. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

rsSDclientsTableOverflow.name: rsSDclientsTableOverflow
rsSDclientsTableOverflow.description: This warning is generated when an overflow occurs in the clients table.

rsSDinactiveServer.name: rsSDinactiveServer
rsSDinactiveServer.description: This warning is generated when a server does not respond to the dispatchers polling and is thought to be inactive.

rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.name: rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow
rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.description: The Zero Hop Routing connections Table has been overflown.

rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted.name: rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted
rsIpZhrReqStaticConnNotAccepted.description: The requested static connection was not accepted because there is no available IP virtual address to allocate to it.

rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource.name: rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource
rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource.description: The virtual IP address appeared as a source IP. All the connections using it will be deleted and it will not be further allocated to new connections.

rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp.name: rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp
rsIpZhrNotAllocVirtualIp.description: The source IP address sent an ARP specifying a virtual IP which was not allocated for this source. This virtual IP will not be allocated to connections of this specific source IP.

rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState.name: rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState
rsSnmpSetRequestInSpecialCfgState.description: An incoming SNMP SET request was rejected because no such requests (except action requests) are accepted after start of new configuration reception or during sending the current configuration to an NMS.

rsWSDRedundancySwitch.name: rsWSDRedundancySwitch
rsWSDRedundancySwitch.description: Whenever main server fails and backup takes over or server comes up after failure a trap of this type is issued.

rsWSDServerStatEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDSerStatAttUsersNum.description: The total number of currently active users attached to this server.

rsWSDSerStatPeakLoad.name: rsWSDSerStatPeakLoad
rsWSDSerStatPeakLoad.description: Maximal number of frames per second dispatched to server since last reset.

rsWSDSerStatFramesRate.name: rsWSDSerStatFramesRate
rsWSDSerStatFramesRate.description: Number of frames per second dispatched to server.

rsWSDSerStatFramesLoad.name: rsWSDSerStatFramesLoad
rsWSDSerStatFramesLoad.description: Number of frames per second dispatched to server.

rsWSDSerStatRecoveryTime.name: rsWSDSerStatRecoveryTime
rsWSDSerStatRecoveryTime.description: Number of seconds after server initialization during which ISD won't send any requests.

rsWSDSerStatConnectionLimit.name: rsWSDSerStatConnectionLimit
rsWSDSerStatConnectionLimit.description: The maximal number of client sessions which can be opened on this sever.

rsWSDSerStatAdminStatus.name: rsWSDSerStatAdminStatus
rsWSDSerStatAdminStatus.description: Enable / Shutdown all the applications on this physical server.

wsdRedundTable.name: wsdRedundTable
wsdRedundTable.description: List of Farm IP addresses backed up by this router.

wsdRedundEntry.name: wsdRedundEntry
wsdRedundEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

wsdRedundFarmAddr.name: wsdRedundFarmAddr

wsdRedundMainWsdAddr.name: wsdRedundMainWsdAddr
wsdRedundMainWsdAddr.description: The Ip address of the polled main wsd.

wsdRedundTimeout.description: Interval in seconds during which the backed-up wsd must signal. If it does not signal, it is considered inactive and the IP interface starts operating as backup.

rsWSDNewEntryOnSourcePort.name: rsWSDNewEntryOnSourcePort
rsWSDNewEntryOnSourcePort.description: Check source port and if different open new client entry.

rsWSDSelectServerOnSourcePort.name: rsWSDSelectServerOnSourcePort
rsWSDSelectServerOnSourcePort.description: Check source port and if different select a new server.

rsNsdMode.description: The Topology chosen for the NSD. Slow mode keeps the servers behind the NSD. Fast mode uses retargeting to connect clients directly to servers.

rsWSDSyslogStatus.name: rsWSDSyslogStatus
rsWSDSyslogStatus.description: Enable/Disable syslog message sending to remote station.

rsWSDSyslogAddress.name: rsWSDSyslogAddress
rsWSDSyslogAddress.description: The IP Address of the syslog station.

rsWSDNTCheckTable.name: rsWSDNTCheckTable
rsWSDNTCheckTable.description: In this table the WSD collects NT statistics per servers.

rsWSDNTCheckEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rsWSDNTSerialNum.description: The serial number of the algorithm.

rsWSDNTFrequentCheckPeriod.description: The period for getting the frequent NT variables.

rsWSDNTOpenSessionsWeight.name: rsWSDNTOpenSessionsWeight
rsWSDNTOpenSessionsWeight.description: The weight for currently open sessions consideration.

rsWSDNTIncomingTrafficWeight.description: The weight for incoming traffic consideration.
